1
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:23,880
In spite of you not being a king

2
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:27,110
my father sends you
his greetings.

3
00:00:28,940 --> 00:00:30,970
And now, let me greet you.

4
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:35,920
I am sorry to hear that your
father died in the forest.

5
00:00:40,070 --> 00:00:42,070
When the sun distances
itself from the earth

6
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,010
the earth is covered
with darkness.

7
00:00:46,140 --> 00:00:48,120
When a father is away
from a son

8
00:00:48,870 --> 00:00:53,110
the son's life is covered
with darkness.

9
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:58,080
Thus, intelligent people keep
a part of the sun

10
00:00:58,940 --> 00:01:02,010
which is a lamp, they
always keep it with them.

11
00:01:03,070 --> 00:01:06,850
Sir, I too have kept a part

12
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:09,810
of my father with me.

13
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,940
The dices.

14
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:18,040
They have been made from
the ashes of my late father.

15
00:01:20,970 --> 00:01:22,070
When alive

16
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,970
my father agreed with me
most of the times.

17
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:32,940
And now, he agrees
to everything I say.

18
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:38,040
Five.

19
00:02:02,970 --> 00:02:04,810
The son of Bharadwaj

20
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:09,750
the great teacher Dronacharya
arrives!

21
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,810
Greetings, Sire.

22
00:02:23,740 --> 00:02:25,880
We welcome you, Dronacharya.
- Thank you.

23
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,850
The king wishes to know

24
00:02:29,740 --> 00:02:33,810
what progress the princess have
made at your hermitage?

25
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:34,970
The king would also like to know

26
00:02:35,740 --> 00:02:37,810
what is the capability
of each prince.

27
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,940
May king Dhritarashtra prosper.

28
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:55,870
My great father

29
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,820
the great sage Bharadwaj
would feel proud

30
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:02,840
such is the knowledge I have
imparted to the princes, O King.

31
00:03:03,970 --> 00:03:06,950
The souls of your departed
ancestors would be pleased

32
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:09,940
such is the knowledge
derived by the princes.

33
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:13,740
I am sure my son Duryodhan
is the best of all.

34
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:15,220
Isn't he?

35
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,740
Why are you quiet,
O great teacher Dronacharya?

36
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,780
Your Majesty, I am quiet

37
00:03:28,670 --> 00:03:29,810
as I wonder whether I should

38
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,710
sing the praises of my students

39
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:36,120
or should my students
exhibit the knowledge

40
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,880
I imparted them and thus
earn praises for my teaching.

41
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,710
What would be appropriate?

42
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:47,680
The teacher is right.

43
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,780
It's a tradition.

44
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,770
When the princes return
on completing their studies

45
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,850
before the subjects
of the kingdom

46
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:58,680
and before the special
guests invited

47
00:03:58,740 --> 00:03:59,910
they should exhibit
their skills.

48
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,870
Exhibition!

49
00:04:08,670 --> 00:04:11,780
We have a different
tradition at Gandhar.

50
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:15,870
Hastinapur follows its
traditions, prince of Gandhar!

51
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,620
Sir, it's the king of Gandhar.

52
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,780
King of Gandhar.

53
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:24,720
Thanks to your blessings
and favors

54
00:04:25,770 --> 00:04:27,680
I am now the king of Gandhar.

55
00:04:27,770 --> 00:04:31,680
I am informing the fine
traditions of my kingdom

56
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:35,740
to the king of Hastinapur.

57
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:39,810
Your majesty, in my kingdom
it is believed

58
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:42,780
that two people can
make similar swords

59
00:04:43,770 --> 00:04:46,770
but no two swordsmen

60
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,670
can be alike.

61
00:04:50,870 --> 00:04:54,870
Thus, your majesty, we hold a
competition at our kingdom

62
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:59,610
especially so that, when the
winner is hailed

63
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:03,680
the entire world learns

64
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:07,810
who has acquired how much
competence.

65
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:12,680
Now if the princes of Hastinapur

66
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:17,680
wish to exhibit their skills
like dancers

67
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,650
his highness would know better.
- King of Gandhar!

68
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:23,680
Hastinapur... - Has a great
tradition, Sire!

69
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:25,750
It's an excellent tradition.

70
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:31,570
The pleasure that lies
in a competition

71
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:32,710
doesn't lie in an exhibition.

72
00:05:40,770 --> 00:05:44,550
We will hold a competition
among the princes.

73
00:05:47,770 --> 00:05:49,540
Besides

74
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:53,650
I wouldn't be able to see them
exhibit their skills, Sire.

75
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,770
But on hearing the people
hail my sons

76
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,600
my heart would feel content.

77
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:04,740
Dronacharya

78
00:06:04,770 --> 00:06:08,580
organize a competition that
you find appropriate.

79
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:11,710
The princes would mock fight
each other in the competition.

80
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,710
I would like to know

81
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:21,480
which prince is eligible to be

82
00:06:21,670 --> 00:06:23,650
heir to the throne
of Hastinapur.

83
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:45,600
A competition!

84
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,640
Vidur, why are we
talking about a competition?

85
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,570
My elder brother

86
00:06:57,640 --> 00:07:01,710
is eager to prove that Duryodhan
is the most eligible one, Sire.

87
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:07,510
I am apprehensive,
before all the invited guests

88
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,550
and the subjects

89
00:07:09,670 --> 00:07:12,550
if there develops an animosity
between the princes

90
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:17,480
it would have dire
consequences, Sire.

91
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:18,640
In any situation

92
00:07:19,570 --> 00:07:22,480
this competition shouldn't
become a duel, Vidur.

93
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:27,410
We have to supervise
it all the time.

94
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:41,550
Greetings, Sire.
- May you live long, dear.

95
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:47,470
I will not let the arrival of
the princes turn into politics.

96
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,550
I promise you.

97
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:52,540
Kunti.

98
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:58,420
Once I had asked you
to trust me and you did.

99
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,540
Today, what has suddenly
happened

100
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:06,640
for you to not have faith in me?

101
00:08:08,470 --> 00:08:10,640
But Sire, the test
of the princes.

102
00:08:13,470 --> 00:08:15,540
It would be appropriate
that my sons

103
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,640
don't take part
in this competition.

104
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:25,580
I hope people do not consider
their capabilities as ambitions

105
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,580
and be enemies with them.

106
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,380
I fear of that, Sire.

107
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,420
Who are you scared of,
sister-in-law?

108
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:42,420
Are you scared of Shakuni,
the king of Gandhar?

109
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:54,380
Don't have any kind of fear,
Kunti.

110
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:58,610
The snake whose venom
is extracted once

111
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:04,420
the next time it gives up its
venom very easily.

112
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:07,520
Because its previous experience

113
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,580
stops it from opposing.

114
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,580
Don't fear Shakuni.

115
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:15,410
Besides

116
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,480
he can no longer conspire.

117
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,510
He too would understand the
burden of responsibilities.

118
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:28,380
He is now the king of a state.

119
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,380
The great Bheeshma had made

120
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,470
a grave mistake by expelling me.

121
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:38,350
Pardon me, your majesty.

122
00:09:40,470 --> 00:09:43,540
But my status will always
be less than the great Bheeshma.

123
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:46,480
Thus, before becoming a part
of your scheme

124
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,440
I would have to think
a hundred times.

125
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:57,310
An ant doesn't get trampled

126
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,470
under the feet of
an elephant, Purochan.

127
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:04,420
You are a man of low stature.

128
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:09,450
The great Bheeshma won't
be watching you.

129
00:10:19,470 --> 00:10:21,450
Think about it.

130
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:24,380
If you help me in my plans

131
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:28,340
you will be enormously
prosperous.

132
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:32,280
And if you do not...

133
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:40,310
What are you planning,
your majesty?

134
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,510
Leave us alone!

135
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:56,280
The king wishes

136
00:10:56,440 --> 00:11:01,350
to hear the people hail Prince
Duryodhan at the playground

137
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,340
and not anyone else.

138
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:10,480
Thus, the entrance door that you
will build for the playground

139
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,470
should collapse at
the right time.

140
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:19,280
